attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles the table, unscrews the top hex socket heads, detaches the tabletop, disassembles all of the four legs, and finally detaches the shelf, and puts all the parts separately.

attributes.Transcription: Hello. Thank you for being part of our study.  In front of you. You'll see the nightstand by IKEA.
Your task, for now, will be to please disassemble it.
You'll find the Allen key on your left.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the top hex socket heads.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should slide plate flat.

attributes.Transcription: Please, slide plate flat as you disassemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the top hex socket heads.
The student disassembles the first leg.

attributes.Transcription: Please, lay the piece on the longer side.
Please, lay the shelf that currently disassembling on its longer end.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the second leg.
The student disassembles the third leg.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should rotate the shelf such that the two feet are on the left-hand side.

attributes.Transcription: Please, rotate the shelf such that the two feet are on the left-hand side.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the fourth leg.

attributes.Transcription: That was everything for this task. Please, press the stop button.
